hello John  I have seen some that were so clogged that even the clutch  cable 
rotor rooter didn't work. Take the old cable and put a little bend in the  
end and try it on a drill/   I had one that we never could get  unclogged but 
the old cable that was broken would go thur so we spliced the  cable right above 
the trans with a barrel connector like the carb hooks up  with  later  mark d



